WEBVTT

00:22.666 --> 00:23.916
Jack?

00:25.333 --> 00:29.208
Jack, you were
supposed to meet me
at the club for doubles.

00:29.291 --> 00:32.708
Those insurance fellas
clobbered me.

00:32.791 --> 00:34.833
You know, one day off
isn't gonna kill you.

00:36.791 --> 00:38.416
- Oh hey.
- Hey.

00:38.500 --> 00:42.041
I was just borrowing
Jack's Betamax.

00:42.125 --> 00:45.125
What happened?
Jack stood you up?

00:45.208 --> 00:47.666
Yeah. Have you seen him?

00:47.750 --> 00:50.083
- Hm, no.
- I called his house.

00:50.166 --> 00:53.666
I figured maybe inspiration
struck and he came here.

00:53.750 --> 00:55.541
Man's not really one
for a day off, you know?

00:55.625 --> 00:58.375
Hey, you're welcome
to take a load off.

00:58.458 --> 01:00.291
You can listen to me
get my 27 words in.

01:00.375 --> 01:02.083
- Twenty-seven, huh?
- Mm-hmm.

01:02.166 --> 01:04.666
Chick choked on his
vodka at commercial.

01:04.750 --> 01:07.333
- That sounds like
a divine intervention.
- Yeah, well.

01:07.416 --> 01:10.083
For a second there, I had
a whole flash of panic.

01:10.166 --> 01:11.583
I was like...

01:11.666 --> 01:13.041
what happens if
he drops dead?

01:13.125 --> 01:16.041
I mean, I'm gonna have to finish
the whole game on my own.

01:16.125 --> 01:18.291
The apprentice's dilemma.

01:18.375 --> 01:20.833
- What's that?
- It's a little...

01:20.916 --> 01:22.375
lecture I used to give.

01:22.458 --> 01:24.166
Well, I love a good lecture.

01:24.250 --> 01:25.625
You can I ask my wife.

01:25.708 --> 01:27.666
Let me get the tequila.
You want some?

01:27.750 --> 01:29.000
- Yeah, alright.

01:29.083 --> 01:30.916
Tudor England.

01:31.000 --> 01:34.166
The entire economy
split into two tiers.

01:34.250 --> 01:36.333
Apprentices and masters.

01:36.416 --> 01:38.875
The idea was that any
apprentice worth his salt

01:38.958 --> 01:41.458
is climbing up that ladder,
turns into a master

01:41.541 --> 01:43.250
when he comes of age.

01:43.333 --> 01:45.666
So, we're too old
to share an office?

01:45.750 --> 01:47.458
Not if you ask Hamlet. See,

01:47.541 --> 01:49.291
you got the whole of Denmark
telling this prince

01:49.375 --> 01:51.791
he's destined to be king.
But, you know what?

01:51.875 --> 01:53.833
He didn't want it.

01:53.916 --> 01:57.708
- He wasn't built for it.
- Mm-hmm.

01:57.791 --> 02:00.791
<i>I think that I spent, uh...</i>

02:00.875 --> 02:04.583
a very long time
feeling like a failure

02:04.666 --> 02:07.166
because the best thing
that I know how to do

02:08.125 --> 02:11.541
is help another guy be great.

02:11.625 --> 02:13.583
But what I'm starting to realize

02:13.666 --> 02:16.916
is that maybe...

02:17.000 --> 02:21.250
'tis better be a noble prince
than hapless king?

02:21.333 --> 02:22.750
Maybe I ought to read
more Shakespeare.

02:22.833 --> 02:24.875
Always.

02:24.958 --> 02:27.750
But that was
a Paul Westhead original.

02:29.333 --> 02:31.750
- Good one.

02:31.833 --> 02:33.333
Well, hello, Jack.

02:33.416 --> 02:34.750
- Cassie.
<i>...he's in ICU.</i>

02:34.833 --> 02:36.750
- Cassie, slow down.
- <i> It's Jack!</i>

02:36.833 --> 02:38.166
<i>Jack's in</i>
<i>the emergency room.</i>

02:38.250 --> 02:39.500
Okay, which hospital?

02:39.583 --> 02:41.208
<i>Little Company of Mary.</i>
<i>T-Torrance.</i>

02:41.291 --> 02:43.000
Yeah. Okay, I'll be right there.

02:44.416 --> 02:47.041
("My Favorite Mutiny"
by The Coup playing

04:14.916 --> 04:16.541
Your name.

04:16.625 --> 04:19.000
Most precious thing
you've got.

04:19.083 --> 04:21.708
That's why it's our job
to protect it.

04:21.791 --> 04:24.250
Keep it synonymous
with success,

04:24.333 --> 04:25.916
on the floor and off.

04:26.000 --> 04:29.083
And I can promise,
when folks see you
in our shoes, they'll say,

04:29.166 --> 04:32.166
"There goes
a Converse All-Star."

04:32.250 --> 04:34.083
"Adidas, the shoe
of champions."

04:34.166 --> 04:35.625
He's cool,
he's fun, and...

04:35.708 --> 04:37.958
- A quality fit. That's Puma.
- ...of course, he's rich.

04:38.041 --> 04:39.416
We need to think
about your feet.

04:39.500 --> 04:40.958
You need to think about
your pocketbook.

04:41.041 --> 04:42.375
- Your legacy.
- Your feet.

04:42.458 --> 04:44.458
You wanna be as American
as apple pie.

04:44.541 --> 04:45.666
That's the makings
of a legend.

04:45.750 --> 04:47.500
...and everyone
will want a piece...

04:47.583 --> 04:50.000
- ...Magic, Mr. Magic.
- The Magic Man!

04:50.083 --> 04:51.750
It's Earvin, actually.

04:51.833 --> 04:53.416
Not anymore! Earvin--

04:53.500 --> 04:55.708
- Earvin will be gone someday.
- Maybe he already is.

04:55.791 --> 04:56.958
Magic is immortal.

04:57.041 --> 04:58.333
If you choose wisely...

04:58.416 --> 05:00.125
- ...this could be...
- If you choose us...

05:00.208 --> 05:02.458
Right on the soles of
the next generation...

05:02.541 --> 05:04.375
- If you choose us...
- This could be

05:04.458 --> 05:06.875
- the most important
choice of your season.
- ...of your entire life.

05:06.958 --> 05:08.916
Well, uh... yeah.

05:10.000 --> 05:12.708
Thanks.
Got a lot to think on.

05:12.791 --> 05:14.625
- Take your time but,
just so you know...
- Sleep on it.

05:14.708 --> 05:17.916
- Just so you know,
Converse already has...
- ...a verbal commitment...

05:18.000 --> 05:19.708
- ...from your friend Larry Bird.
- ...Larry Bird.

05:21.833 --> 05:22.833
Oh.

05:22.916 --> 05:24.833
That's Magic Johnson!

05:27.000 --> 05:29.125
Hope you had your fill
of bullshit.

05:29.208 --> 05:30.458
Those guys keep on shoveling

05:30.541 --> 05:33.208
till you're just another
stallion in the stable.

05:33.291 --> 05:35.416
Phil.
Phil Knight.

05:35.500 --> 05:37.958
Hey, Phil. You...
you on the schedule?

05:38.041 --> 05:39.416
Me?
Heck no.

05:39.500 --> 05:42.333
Front Office seems to have you
under lock and key.

05:42.416 --> 05:43.708
Big dogs only.

05:43.791 --> 05:46.375
Fact is, I-I'm sort
of a rookie myself.

05:46.458 --> 05:48.250
Let me be straight as
an arrow with you, Earvin.

05:48.333 --> 05:49.750
C-can I call you Earvin?

05:49.833 --> 05:51.458
I wish somebody would.

05:51.541 --> 05:53.458
Good 'cause I'm an athlete, too.
Ran track at Oregon.

05:53.541 --> 05:56.833
Mediocre talent. Not like you.
But, my coach and me,

05:56.916 --> 05:59.208
my partner now,
we figured out a nifty trick.

05:59.291 --> 06:00.625
If we could shave just one ounce

06:00.708 --> 06:03.166
off of our shoes, it made us
55 pounds lighter every mile.

06:03.250 --> 06:04.666
You run an average
of three miles a game.

06:04.750 --> 06:07.916
Think how much faster
you would be without
any extra weight.

06:08.000 --> 06:09.541
What, you tellin' me
to play barefoot?

06:09.625 --> 06:12.666
I'm telling you to play...
in these.

06:30.333 --> 06:33.458
- Y'all making me a special pair?
- Every pair.

06:33.541 --> 06:36.666
The Nike Magic.

06:36.750 --> 06:39.916
A new label for
a whole new line.

06:41.833 --> 06:45.708
- Y'all talking to
Larry Bird, too?
- I'm talking to you.

06:45.791 --> 06:48.333
We need more than just
a smile on a poster.

06:48.416 --> 06:50.541
We need a partner.

06:52.208 --> 06:53.791
- How much we talking?
- You mean

06:53.875 --> 06:55.666
can I give you what those
other guys are offering.

06:55.750 --> 06:58.708
Where's that sitting right now?
Sixty, 70 grand a year?

06:58.791 --> 07:00.041
Eighty.

07:01.083 --> 07:04.500
Wow.
I'm offering a dollar.

07:04.583 --> 07:05.958
One for every pair we ship,

07:06.041 --> 07:07.833
plus 100,000 in stock options.

07:07.916 --> 07:10.000
Right now,
that's 18 cents a share.

07:10.083 --> 07:12.458
But the sky's the limit, Earvin.

07:13.083 --> 07:14.416
Bet on us,

07:14.500 --> 07:17.875
you're betting on yourself.

07:17.958 --> 07:19.500
Proposal's in the shoe.
Look it over,

07:19.583 --> 07:20.875
I'll be in town all week.

07:22.333 --> 07:24.708
Ah! Sign with us,
you get the right one, too!

07:40.041 --> 07:41.875
Oh, good lord.

07:45.041 --> 07:46.958
Is he...

07:48.625 --> 07:50.750
Oh, no! I mean, he...

07:50.833 --> 07:53.000
Wow, he looks really good.

07:53.083 --> 07:56.041
- Actually...
- Okay, let's go.
Let's go get some air.

07:56.125 --> 07:58.708
- Paul's here now.
- I'm here. I'm sorry.

07:58.791 --> 08:00.750
Hey, Cran, it's gonna be okay.

08:00.833 --> 08:03.291
- Come on, Cran.
Let's get some air.
- I'm here.

08:03.375 --> 08:06.083
Hey, I got this.
We're going to be fine.

08:19.916 --> 08:22.708
Goddammit, Jack.

08:22.791 --> 08:25.000
You were supposed to meet me
for tennis, man.

08:27.666 --> 08:29.500
- Okay.
- Good afternoon.

08:29.583 --> 08:30.625
Hi. Hey.

08:30.708 --> 08:32.791
- Are you family?
- Um, if you could...

08:32.875 --> 08:34.791
just give me
the information, please.

08:34.875 --> 08:37.000
Well, we were able
to dress his wounds,

08:37.083 --> 08:39.208
but the inflammation in his
brain is worrisome. Are...

08:40.375 --> 08:41.916
Are you authorized
to make decisions?

08:42.000 --> 08:44.333
- We may need to
discuss goals of care.
- Okay.

08:44.416 --> 08:46.083
My goal is to get him up
and walking out of here

08:46.166 --> 08:48.000
- as good as new, right?
- Of course.

08:48.083 --> 08:50.333
That's our north star,

08:50.416 --> 08:52.000
but an injury severe as this,

08:52.083 --> 08:55.083
sometimes, the discussion
moves to quality of life.

08:56.416 --> 08:59.875
Quality of life?
He's head coach of the Lakers.

08:59.958 --> 09:01.958
He's living his dr--
All he did was take a tumble

09:02.041 --> 09:04.666
- off of a goddamn bike!
- The trauma he's endured--

09:04.750 --> 09:06.250
It's not gonna happen!
If that's your attitude,

09:06.333 --> 09:08.291
we're going to need
another doctor. Just...

09:12.208 --> 09:15.250
That's Jack McKinney.
He's my best friend. So,

09:15.333 --> 09:17.291
what I need to hear from you

09:17.375 --> 09:19.625
is what you're gonna do
to fix him up

09:19.708 --> 09:21.791
because we have
a fucking game tomorrow!

09:41.500 --> 09:43.250
Well, well, well.

09:43.333 --> 09:47.208
- What do we have here?
- It's from the<i> signore.</i>

09:47.291 --> 09:49.083
It's on me, pal.

09:50.958 --> 09:53.958
Jack. You shouldn't have!

09:54.041 --> 09:56.333
I had to comp
his season tickets
to get him to do that.

09:56.416 --> 09:58.458
He's our biggest fan.
It's crazy.

09:58.541 --> 10:00.666
We got two seats
right next to him.

10:00.750 --> 10:02.458
Reserved for Great Western Bank.

10:02.541 --> 10:05.958
Hot damn!
The wife is gonna plotz.

10:06.041 --> 10:08.625
You know, Dr. Buss put
chairs right on the floor

10:08.708 --> 10:11.083
- because it's great
for television.

10:11.166 --> 10:13.041
Yeah. We don't pick
that up in Sacramento.

10:13.125 --> 10:15.125
All they pick up in Sacramento
is the clap,

10:15.208 --> 10:17.708
which, incidentally, is
exactly how this is spreading.

10:17.791 --> 10:19.458
<i>We're 13 games in.</i>

10:19.541 --> 10:20.791
<i>We got lightning in a bottle.</i>

10:20.875 --> 10:22.958
<i>We got a genius coach,</i>
<i>young phenom,</i>

10:23.041 --> 10:25.791
<i>coupled with the greatest</i>
<i>player in the league,</i>

10:25.875 --> 10:27.583
right here,
smack dab in the heart

10:27.666 --> 10:29.500
of the entertainment
capital of the world.

10:29.583 --> 10:30.875
Mr. Buss,

10:30.958 --> 10:32.833
we are a banking institution,

10:32.916 --> 10:34.250
and your loan
matures tomorrow.

10:34.333 --> 10:37.041
Though I presume from your
request to meet that we're here

10:37.125 --> 10:38.708
to talk about a payment plan.

10:38.791 --> 10:42.083
You're darn tootin'.
Frank, tell him our plan.

10:43.291 --> 10:44.958
We don't plan to pay.

10:48.583 --> 10:50.833
We're giving you an opportunity.

10:52.041 --> 10:54.583
The Lakers are the team
of the 1980s,

10:54.666 --> 10:57.541
and the Great Western Bank can
be the official banking partner

10:57.625 --> 10:59.583
of the Los Angeles Lakers.

10:59.666 --> 11:01.333
But we're gonna need
a continuation

11:01.416 --> 11:04.500
of the current loan through
June to the end of the season,

11:04.583 --> 11:06.000
plus a fresh line of credit,

11:06.083 --> 11:07.500
so we can keep investing
in the business.

11:07.583 --> 11:09.750
Together.

11:09.833 --> 11:13.125
And if we demand our money now?

11:13.208 --> 11:15.875
Well then, Mariani,
Buss, and Associates

11:15.958 --> 11:17.875
is going to file for bankruptcy.

11:17.958 --> 11:21.458
And you can take the two of us
for everything we got.

11:21.541 --> 11:23.458
Which, right now, is...

11:23.541 --> 11:25.250
I don't know, Frank,
what do we got?

11:30.458 --> 11:31.875
- $72.
- Oh,

11:31.958 --> 11:33.833
and this fine bottle of
bubbly. Don't forget that.

11:33.916 --> 11:37.541
And, of course, the team.
The team is worth plenty.

11:37.625 --> 11:39.416
N...ope!

11:39.500 --> 11:41.666
My mother is a genius,
by the way.

11:41.750 --> 11:44.125
My ex-wife wanted
something gold,

11:44.208 --> 11:46.166
so I gave her the team.

11:46.250 --> 11:48.250
All that's in her name now.

11:48.333 --> 11:52.125
So, you can shake us down
and come up with pocket lint,

11:52.208 --> 11:54.750
or you can dig down deep

11:54.833 --> 11:56.791
into those fancy suits you got,

11:56.875 --> 11:59.000
try to find the balls

11:59.083 --> 12:01.208
to stay in business
with the Lakers.

12:01.291 --> 12:02.541
And then, my friends,

12:02.625 --> 12:05.875
that bank is gonna raise
a statue of you two

12:05.958 --> 12:08.375
right there in downtown
Sacramento someday.
Trust me.

12:08.458 --> 12:10.083
Listen, I'd love
to stay and chitchat,

12:10.166 --> 12:12.666
but I have a very horny
22-year-old upstairs

12:12.750 --> 12:13.875
just waiting for me. So,

12:13.958 --> 12:16.375
take our projections,
spend the day with them,

12:16.458 --> 12:19.041
and then come to
the club tonight
and tell us we got a deal.

12:19.125 --> 12:20.750
The Jacksons are gonna
pack that place.

12:20.833 --> 12:22.833
But don't worry.
We got your comp tickets.

12:22.916 --> 12:24.083
Listen,

12:24.166 --> 12:26.625
it's clear skies
from here on out.

12:26.708 --> 12:29.291
Pleasure doing business
with you. Frank.

12:33.666 --> 12:35.250
Oh, boy, oh boy, oh boy.

12:35.333 --> 12:36.625
You think
they're gonna go for it?

12:36.708 --> 12:38.250
Of course, they're
gonna go for it.

12:38.333 --> 12:40.333
They'd be fools not to.
We got 'em by
the short and curlies.

12:40.416 --> 12:42.166
- Hello, gentlemen.
- Claire?

12:42.250 --> 12:44.083
- What are you doing here?
- I'm waiting for you.

12:44.166 --> 12:45.500
On my day off.

12:45.583 --> 12:47.166
Was supposed to be at
the zoo with my grandson,

12:47.250 --> 12:49.916
- but there's a problem
with food and beverage.
- What's that?

12:50.000 --> 12:51.500
- There isn't any.
- Fuck.

12:51.583 --> 12:53.041
He hears me on the phone.
Kid's like a parrot.

12:53.125 --> 12:54.916
The deliveries were never made
because your bookkeeper

12:55.000 --> 12:57.750
sent bad checks
to all my vendors.

12:57.833 --> 13:00.125
- None of the vendors
have been paid?
- No.

13:01.333 --> 13:04.083
Th-th--
This is an old account.

13:05.416 --> 13:07.041
She's an old bookkeeper.

13:10.166 --> 13:12.416
<i>I was telling Earvin</i>
<i>that it is some luck</i>

13:12.500 --> 13:15.666
<i>that you're in town.</i>
<i>You know, your head</i>
<i>for business.</i>

13:15.750 --> 13:17.416
These shoe companies
are comin' at him

13:17.500 --> 13:20.791
pretty hard for
an endorsement deal.

13:20.875 --> 13:23.041
I can imagine.
Promise you the world.

13:23.125 --> 13:25.125
The question is,
will they deliver?

13:25.208 --> 13:27.000
Yeah.

13:27.083 --> 13:29.041
Whole lot of numbers, but...

13:29.125 --> 13:32.666
Have you been talking to anybody
else about this? A professional?

13:32.750 --> 13:36.125
Um, Pops got Mr. Bowman
outta D-Town.

13:36.208 --> 13:39.000
He's a fine attorney
for a Michigan attorney.

13:40.291 --> 13:41.416
And for this?

13:41.500 --> 13:44.041
Don't know his dick
from a doorknob.

13:45.500 --> 13:48.500
Guess you could say
the same thing about me, too.

13:49.583 --> 13:50.916
I wouldn't.

13:51.625 --> 13:53.166
Look ...

13:53.250 --> 13:54.916
Let me pose a question

13:55.041 --> 13:57.500
that I pose to all
my clients, okay?

13:57.583 --> 14:00.750
Five years, 10 years, 50.

14:00.833 --> 14:04.166
What do you want
out of your future?

14:07.708 --> 14:09.250
Um...

14:09.333 --> 14:11.625
everything.

14:11.708 --> 14:13.833
Okay. That's big business.

14:13.916 --> 14:15.541
Something for everybody.

14:15.625 --> 14:16.708
Kinda like Coca-Cola.

14:16.791 --> 14:18.208
That's right! Yeah! Just--

14:18.291 --> 14:19.625
That's exactly what
I'm talking about!

14:19.708 --> 14:21.375
Good, so now we know what
we building here, right?

14:21.458 --> 14:23.708
- Our promised land.
- Right.

14:23.791 --> 14:25.416
We need our 10 Commandments.

14:25.500 --> 14:27.375
Pitfalls to avoid.

14:27.458 --> 14:29.625
Choices that
Earvin might make

14:29.708 --> 14:32.416
that would be bad
for Magic Johnson.

14:36.375 --> 14:38.875
You ain't gotta worry
about that with me.

14:38.958 --> 14:40.166
I don't drink none,

14:40.250 --> 14:42.958
and I don't touch
that narcotic either.

14:44.500 --> 14:47.375
- Some Coca-Cola for you.

14:50.166 --> 14:52.208
And women?

14:53.750 --> 14:56.375
You gotta be smarter.

14:57.375 --> 14:58.708
Quieter.

14:58.791 --> 15:01.416
Keep everybody happy.

15:05.500 --> 15:08.250
- Want another cup, Pops?
- Better not, baby girl.

15:08.333 --> 15:11.166
The jet-lag is
beating me down. So,

15:11.250 --> 15:14.125
why don't I take a closer
look at these, Earvin?

15:14.208 --> 15:17.083
You know, we could talk
at the game tomorrow.

15:17.166 --> 15:19.250
Cindy here has promised me
some good seats.

15:19.333 --> 15:22.208
You see, my man
takes care of family.

15:22.291 --> 15:25.208
Yeah. Hey, Doc, actually,
you d-- you don't gotta...

15:26.416 --> 15:29.458
It's not a problem
at all. Trust me.

15:29.541 --> 15:31.375
- Let's go.
- You got everything, Dad?

15:31.458 --> 15:33.333
I do, sweetheart.
Walk me out.

15:45.833 --> 15:47.250
- Ma!

15:47.333 --> 15:49.791
No, no, no! Don't close that!

15:49.875 --> 15:51.208
- Ma!

15:51.291 --> 15:54.041
- Oh my god, my god...
- How bad is it?

15:54.125 --> 15:55.958
- Move this.
We need to get...

15:56.041 --> 15:58.000
- Dad! Sorry!
I couldn't hear you!
- The hell is going on?

15:58.083 --> 16:01.375
- If that's Gerald,
tell him to get in here!
- I can't smell it.

16:01.458 --> 16:04.375
- Smell what!?
- She doesn't know
the smell of death.

16:04.458 --> 16:06.958
- I do. Don't close that door!

16:07.041 --> 16:09.875
