32:02.666 --> 32:04.541
Franchise is behind
us both 100%.

32:04.625 --> 32:06.250
So, there's nothing
to the reports that
he's in a coma?

32:06.333 --> 32:08.333
- How about these rumors that
Jack's fighting for his life?
- Rumors?

32:08.416 --> 32:10.208
You know what? I'm not gonna
get caught up in rumors.

32:10.291 --> 32:13.541
We're going to focus
on the task ahead.

32:13.625 --> 32:16.375
And for me right now,
the task ahead

32:16.458 --> 32:17.750
well, it's Denver.

32:17.833 --> 32:20.208
And, uh, Skywalker Thompson.

32:20.291 --> 32:23.083
- He went on a tear
last night in Utah.

32:23.166 --> 32:24.500
Yeah, he sure did.

32:24.583 --> 32:26.500
I think that's probably why, uh,

32:26.583 --> 32:29.500
that's probably why
Jack McKinney is playing hooky

32:29.583 --> 32:31.666
because, uh, he wants
to avoid a repeat.

32:31.750 --> 32:33.416
So, you and Jack talked
about the Utah game?

32:33.500 --> 32:35.791
- Does that mean he's conscious?
- That's after the accident?

32:38.208 --> 32:39.625
- What are you not telling us?
- I'm not saying--

32:39.708 --> 32:41.541
Jack McKinney is on the mend.

32:41.625 --> 32:44.041
- What'd you tell him to say?
- I didn't tell him to say shit.

32:44.125 --> 32:46.416
- Is he in critical condition?
- Paul, you gotta
give us something.

32:46.500 --> 32:48.708
Is he in a vegetable
state or what?

32:48.791 --> 32:50.291
I...

32:50.375 --> 32:53.250
- What do we tell the fans?
- Just tell them...

32:58.958 --> 33:01.458
"If it be now,

33:01.541 --> 33:03.375
"'tis not to come.

33:05.166 --> 33:07.500
"If it be not to come

33:07.583 --> 33:09.041
"it will be now.

33:11.000 --> 33:13.500
"If it not be now,

33:13.583 --> 33:16.375
yet it will come."

33:17.250 --> 33:19.583
- Come on, Paul.

33:19.666 --> 33:21.833
"The readiness...

33:22.416 --> 33:24.375
is all."

33:24.458 --> 33:26.416
- Get up there.
Get him off the stage now.
- Thank you.

33:26.500 --> 33:27.791
Okay! Okay!

33:27.875 --> 33:30.291
We'll see you all at
the game tonight, huh?

33:30.375 --> 33:32.250
What the fuck was that?

33:32.333 --> 33:34.916
- My comfort zone.
- Will he be able to coach again?

33:35.000 --> 33:37.375
- That's it, folks, thank you.
- Wow...

33:37.458 --> 33:39.291
<i>Wise words from</i>
<i>Jack McKinney's substitute.</i>

33:39.375 --> 33:41.833
<i>This time last year,</i>
<i>he was teaching Shakespeare.</i>

33:41.916 --> 33:45.666
<i>- Tonight, he steps in as--</i>
- Oh, that oughta keep
'em chasing their tails.

33:45.750 --> 33:47.416
Yeah, well, I wish they
were the only ones.

33:47.500 --> 33:49.291
I spent all night

33:49.375 --> 33:51.250
trying to decipher

33:51.333 --> 33:53.708
what the hunting pattern
of the Bengal tiger

33:53.791 --> 33:57.916
has to do with keeping
Thompson out of the lane.

33:58.000 --> 34:00.958
- Well, you stick one there,
he'll probably avoid it.

34:01.041 --> 34:02.208
Thanks.

34:02.291 --> 34:04.083
This is Jack shit.
Alright? It's not for you.

34:04.166 --> 34:05.625
- Come on! Goddammit.
- Let it go.

34:05.708 --> 34:08.166
Let it go. What would you do?

34:09.333 --> 34:11.291
- What I would do...
- Your show.

34:14.083 --> 34:16.958
If it was me, I would--
I would do something
off the wall.

34:17.041 --> 34:20.291
- I would-- I would start Cooper.
- Great.

34:20.375 --> 34:21.750
No, you know what?
I would play it safe,

34:21.833 --> 34:23.583
and I would stick with Haywood.

34:25.333 --> 34:26.958
Alright.

34:28.666 --> 34:30.375
No, Cooper.

34:31.166 --> 34:32.791
Or Haywood?

34:33.833 --> 34:35.750
That's a good idea.

34:38.166 --> 34:40.458
Fuck!

34:40.541 --> 34:41.916
You want the job?

34:49.000 --> 34:51.083
<i>You know what you</i>
<i>could do with Thompson?</i>

34:51.166 --> 34:54.166
<i>Drive him baseline to his</i>
<i>weak hand for the trap.</i>

34:54.250 --> 34:56.125
Haywood and Cooper double-team.

34:56.208 --> 34:58.000
<i>He's weaker when</i>
<i>he moves to the left,</i>

34:58.083 --> 34:59.500
<i>so you force him that way.</i>

34:59.583 --> 35:01.500
<i>Overplay the passing lanes.</i>

35:03.375 --> 35:06.541
You know what...
You know what you
could do with Thompson?

35:11.541 --> 35:13.000
The team is here.

35:13.083 --> 35:14.250
Okay.

35:14.333 --> 35:15.375
Oh...

35:15.458 --> 35:17.583
- I'm going to take Cran home.
- Yeah.

35:17.666 --> 35:19.958
Yeah, she--
She definitely needs a break.

35:20.041 --> 35:21.958
- You do, too.
- Yeah.

35:26.875 --> 35:28.583
Nothing good can come
from sitting here,

35:28.666 --> 35:31.208
watching him like this.

35:31.291 --> 35:35.208
"I make as much use of it
as many a man doth...

35:36.041 --> 35:37.958
a<i> memento mori."</i>

35:38.958 --> 35:40.375
It's a Death's Head.

35:40.458 --> 35:42.875
Elizabethans used to
put it everywhere

35:42.958 --> 35:46.916
with that inscription.
<i>Memento mori.</i>
"Remember...

35:47.958 --> 35:50.250
you will die."

35:50.333 --> 35:51.833
Shakespeare sealed
the words in wax

35:51.916 --> 35:54.625
on everything he wrote
after his son died.

35:54.708 --> 35:57.458
No, there's something
beautiful in that.

35:57.541 --> 36:00.291
Life is fleeting,
so make every moment count.

36:01.250 --> 36:03.458
It meant the opposite.

36:03.541 --> 36:05.958
Life is meaningless.

36:06.041 --> 36:08.083
All earthly things are vanity.

36:08.166 --> 36:10.416
<i>Well, that's less cheerful.</i>

36:11.666 --> 36:13.333
<i>I, uh...</i>

36:16.791 --> 36:19.083
I can't believe I have
to coach this game.

36:21.000 --> 36:22.833
You can do it.

36:26.666 --> 36:29.083
You shakin' like a flea-bit dog.

36:29.166 --> 36:30.750
It's all over.

36:30.833 --> 36:33.250
Man, you don't know that.
Coach could pull through.

36:33.333 --> 36:35.416
No, not-not Coach.

36:35.500 --> 36:36.875
It's just...

36:36.958 --> 36:39.875
Me, man.
Westhead ain't no fan.

36:39.958 --> 36:41.375
What makes you say that?

36:41.458 --> 36:43.958
I seen it in camp.
The way he was looking at me,

36:44.041 --> 36:45.791
like I was a loose thread
on a sweater.

36:45.875 --> 36:48.375
I bet you he can't
wait to cut me off.

36:48.458 --> 36:49.750
Is that right?

36:50.333 --> 36:52.125
Hm. Brother,

36:52.208 --> 36:55.250
I ain't known you but a minute,
but what I can say

36:55.333 --> 36:56.583
is you are the nervousest cat

36:56.666 --> 36:59.333
in a building full
of people dying.

36:59.416 --> 37:02.583
Didn't nobody end up
in the NBA by accident.

37:02.666 --> 37:04.708
I don't know, Spence.
Maybe I'm the first.

37:04.791 --> 37:09.083
No, you're not.
You supposed to be here.
You understand?

37:09.166 --> 37:11.000
McKinney or no McKinney.

37:11.083 --> 37:12.791
Coach is just a coach.

37:12.875 --> 37:14.791
All the damn talent you got?

37:14.875 --> 37:17.625
Any fool could see it!
Even Westhead!

37:25.833 --> 37:28.416
Hey. Uh...

37:28.500 --> 37:31.583
Wanna thank you all
for coming. Um...

37:31.666 --> 37:33.791
I know that it's going
to mean a lot to Jack.

37:34.875 --> 37:36.333
How is he?

37:37.666 --> 37:39.333
He's better. He's better.
Thank you.

37:39.416 --> 37:42.666
Um, he's probably
not well enough for visitors

37:42.750 --> 37:45.041
just yet.
So, let's keep him
in our thoughts

37:45.125 --> 37:47.416
and, uh, I'll see you
at the game.

37:54.208 --> 37:55.458
Oh...

37:55.541 --> 37:59.958
I-I'm sorry. I hope I'm not,
uh, interrupting.

38:00.041 --> 38:01.666
These are from Magic.

38:01.750 --> 38:04.291
He is so sorry
that he couldn't be here,

38:04.375 --> 38:06.083
but he just wanted to make sure

38:06.166 --> 38:08.291
that Coach McKinney knows

38:08.375 --> 38:10.500
how much he means to us.

38:10.583 --> 38:13.708
So, you know, there's some
eucalyptus in there, so...

38:13.791 --> 38:16.000
that's good
for his breathing.

38:27.791 --> 38:30.833
I think you're making
a wise choice.

38:30.916 --> 38:34.333
So what I'm supposed to say
to the ones I ain't going with?

38:34.416 --> 38:35.791
Nothing.

38:35.875 --> 38:37.833
You can't muddy up that
million-dollar smile

38:37.916 --> 38:39.916
- delivering bad news.
- Alright.

38:40.000 --> 38:42.708
- Right on!
- That can be my job.

38:49.500 --> 38:51.666
Gentlemen! Welcome.

38:51.750 --> 38:54.166
Come on in! Son,

38:54.250 --> 38:55.541
on behalf of Converse,

38:55.625 --> 38:58.583
we are just thrilled to
welcome you into our stable.

38:59.875 --> 39:02.375
I think we are gonna
make a lot of hay.

39:02.458 --> 39:03.958
Before we put pen to paper,

39:04.041 --> 39:06.125
I took the liberty
of making some adjustments.

39:06.208 --> 39:09.458
For starters, we've learned
that Larry Bird has agreed

39:09.541 --> 39:11.916
to $90,000, and we believe

39:12.000 --> 39:13.666
we should command 100.

39:16.333 --> 39:18.875
- Well, that's quite an ask.
- Well...

39:18.958 --> 39:21.208
my man is quite an athlete.

39:21.291 --> 39:23.125
Well, you drive
a hard bargain,

39:23.208 --> 39:24.916
but you got
yourself a deal.

39:27.458 --> 39:28.750
That's what I'm talkin' about!

39:28.833 --> 39:31.125
- Yeah.
- Some notes.

39:31.208 --> 39:34.333
So, I was thinking...

39:34.416 --> 39:37.041
We put my name
right there on the shoe.

39:37.125 --> 39:38.458
I'm thinking...

39:39.541 --> 39:41.125
"The Magic."

39:43.666 --> 39:46.708
I see it. Look, "The Magic."

39:46.791 --> 39:48.875
Ain't no one else done that!

39:48.958 --> 39:50.250
Well, that's an idea!

39:50.333 --> 39:52.750
We'll run it up the flagpole
back at corporate.

39:52.833 --> 39:56.458
But first, let's get you
on the dotted line.

39:56.541 --> 39:58.000
To Magic.

39:58.083 --> 39:59.375
You won't regret it.

40:09.583 --> 40:10.708
He regrets it.

40:21.000 --> 40:23.583
<i>My father Lydus was a genius.</i>

40:25.250 --> 40:28.000
<i>He had a head for numbers.</i>

40:28.083 --> 40:29.875
I think he liked numbers
more than he liked people,

40:29.958 --> 40:31.583
far as I can tell.

40:31.666 --> 40:34.250
Definitely liked numbers
more than he liked me.

40:36.833 --> 40:39.208
Left us high and dry
when I was born.

40:40.416 --> 40:42.750
Mom was 19.

40:42.833 --> 40:45.541
No high school education.

40:45.625 --> 40:47.833
Now, she's got
this kid to raise.

40:49.500 --> 40:51.708
Middle of the fucking Dust Bowl.

40:55.583 --> 40:57.250
<i>But, she got us here.</i>

40:59.000 --> 41:00.666
<i>She got us here.</i>

41:00.750 --> 41:04.166
- That's one tough broad.
- Dr. Buss?

41:04.833 --> 41:05.916
Hey.

41:07.458 --> 41:08.666
How's she doin'?

41:08.750 --> 41:10.791
Exhausted, but coherent.

41:10.875 --> 41:13.041
There's no outward
sign of trauma.

41:13.125 --> 41:16.041
Oh, good. Good.
Yeah. Right?

41:16.125 --> 41:17.875
Yeah...

41:17.958 --> 41:20.916
I figured she just
forgot to eat.

41:21.000 --> 41:23.833
- Could be.

41:23.916 --> 41:26.416
Why don't you bring her by
for a full workup?

41:26.500 --> 41:28.625
In the meantime,

41:28.708 --> 41:30.833
take care of yourself, too.

41:30.916 --> 41:32.208
You look tired.

41:32.291 --> 41:34.375
See if you can keep it
to a pack a day.

41:35.750 --> 41:37.208
Sure thing, Doc.

41:40.333 --> 41:41.958
<i>See?</i>

41:42.041 --> 41:43.583
She's gonna be fine.

41:43.666 --> 41:46.083
<i>I always wanted to</i>
<i>go out with a bang.</i>

41:48.000 --> 41:50.791
Instead, I seem to be rotting.

41:50.875 --> 41:53.541
No. Bullshit.

41:53.625 --> 41:55.666
Alcohol is a preservative.

41:58.458 --> 42:01.416
Well, at least
I taught you to laugh.

42:01.500 --> 42:03.916
I know I fucked up
everything else.

42:04.000 --> 42:05.500
Come on.

42:07.291 --> 42:09.000
Don't talk like that.

42:10.583 --> 42:12.708
You got me where I am today.

42:13.625 --> 42:15.208
Hm...

42:23.041 --> 42:24.791
Sorry, I'll wait outside.

42:40.750 --> 42:42.375
It's my fault.

42:46.750 --> 42:48.333
Just a spell.

42:49.833 --> 42:52.291
No, it wasn't the first time.

42:53.541 --> 42:56.083
Opening night, she didn't
know what day it was.

42:57.708 --> 42:59.458
She was out of it.

43:02.000 --> 43:05.416
I should've told you,
but I didn't want to ruin
your big day.

43:09.833 --> 43:11.458
Jeanie.

43:12.916 --> 43:14.291
Get it together.

43:14.375 --> 43:16.208
- She's gonna be okay.

44:16.333 --> 44:17.666
What's goin' on, Coach?

44:19.333 --> 44:20.875
Game day. Hey.

44:20.958 --> 44:22.666
Okay.

44:23.583 --> 44:25.083
Gentlemen...

44:29.750 --> 44:33.208
I know that it's hard right now.

44:33.291 --> 44:35.500
I know that
our hearts are heavy.

44:37.791 --> 44:40.291
But, we got a job to do.

44:40.375 --> 44:42.583
And there is nothing--
There is nothing!

44:42.666 --> 44:46.541
That Jack McKinney
would want more than a win.

44:46.625 --> 44:48.375
- That's right.
- Yep!

44:49.500 --> 44:52.000
So, let's take a minute.
Let's take a minute.

44:54.416 --> 44:56.708
"Give sorrow words.

44:56.791 --> 44:58.541
"The grief that does not speak,

44:58.625 --> 45:02.166
whispers the o'erfraught heart
and bids it break."

45:03.958 --> 45:05.500
Hm?

45:06.458 --> 45:08.250
So, Coach dead?

45:08.333 --> 45:09.666
No. No, no, no.

45:09.750 --> 45:12.750
- No. No, no. Not at all.

45:12.833 --> 45:15.291
Yeah.
Who's guarding Thompson?

45:15.375 --> 45:17.875
- I got him, Coach.
- Hell no. You the slowest
in conditioning.

45:17.958 --> 45:19.916
- Who you talking about?
- Bunny is your man.

45:20.000 --> 45:21.166
- You crazy.
- Cooper.

45:22.833 --> 45:24.791
You're starting at four.

45:24.875 --> 45:28.083
- Jim, you're next
in the rotation.
- What?

45:28.166 --> 45:30.625
Where that put me, Coach?

45:30.708 --> 45:32.458
It puts you on the bench.

45:32.541 --> 45:34.041
- Whoa.
- Brutal.

45:34.125 --> 45:35.333
Everybody else,

45:35.416 --> 45:36.875
same as usual. Okay?

45:36.958 --> 45:39.750
- Alright, come on,
bring it in. Bring it in!

45:39.833 --> 45:42.166
Jack on three! One, two, three.

45:42.250 --> 45:43.625
Jack!

45:43.708 --> 45:45.583
- Hey. Hey, Paul?

45:45.666 --> 45:47.500
I can take Thompson. Whoo!

45:47.583 --> 45:49.125
Is there a problem?

45:49.208 --> 45:51.750
Well, I'm not sure if you heard
what I said back at the hospital

45:51.833 --> 45:53.333
between me and the young blood,

45:53.416 --> 45:56.041
but if it's putting us
off on the wrong foot...

45:56.125 --> 45:57.875
Oh...

45:57.958 --> 46:00.750
No, no. This is a--
This is a basketball decision.

46:01.541 --> 46:02.916
It's nothing personal.

46:04.833 --> 46:06.250
Okay?

46:08.458 --> 46:10.333
Hey, uh, Young Buck?

46:10.416 --> 46:13.083
You gonna play this one,
or you gonna let your girl
do it for you?

46:14.708 --> 46:16.208
Girl?

46:16.291 --> 46:18.125
You gonna send your squeeze
to the hospital

46:18.208 --> 46:19.208
and think we ain't gonna say?

46:19.291 --> 46:20.791
Fine ol' redbone, too.

46:20.875 --> 46:22.416
You lucky I ain't holler at her.

46:22.500 --> 46:25.583
- Well,
she sat next to me, so...
- Cindy?

46:25.666 --> 46:27.208
I ain't even know
she went to the hospital.

46:27.291 --> 46:29.750
With 10 funerals of flowers.

46:29.833 --> 46:31.416
Rip Van Winkle ever wake up,

46:31.500 --> 46:33.208
- he gonna think
he in a garden.

46:33.291 --> 46:34.833
Nice touch, Young Blood.

46:34.916 --> 46:37.291
Not as nice as showing up
yourself though.

46:37.375 --> 46:39.250
Say it again, Cap.

46:45.416 --> 46:47.791
I'd like to be friends with her!

46:47.875 --> 46:49.291
Hey, babe.

46:51.125 --> 46:52.250
Hey.

46:52.333 --> 46:54.041
What's... What's wrong?

46:54.125 --> 46:56.000
Y'all brought too many flowers.

46:56.083 --> 46:57.666
- I ain't asked you to do that.
- Well, I was--

46:57.750 --> 46:59.666
You got me up in there
looking crazy

46:59.750 --> 47:00.958
in front of all my teammates.

47:01.041 --> 47:02.375
I was just trying
to be gracious.

47:02.458 --> 47:05.083
- I was representing you--
- There he is!

47:05.166 --> 47:06.750
The Converse Man.

47:06.833 --> 47:09.208
The lovely young Miss Buss
has been giving me the tour.

47:10.250 --> 47:12.166
Nice shoes.
Congratulations.

47:12.250 --> 47:14.583
Thanks. I got some good advice.

47:14.666 --> 47:16.541
Nonsense. He's a natural.
Between the three of you,

47:16.625 --> 47:18.958
our future is in good hands.

47:21.500 --> 47:23.750
Why don't I, uh,
show you to your seats?

47:23.833 --> 47:24.916
Thank you.

47:26.166 --> 47:27.541
Hey, Doc.
You got a minute?

47:27.625 --> 47:29.458
Something the matter, son?

47:30.250 --> 47:31.458
Nah...

47:31.541 --> 47:34.541
Look... Yeah.

47:35.208 --> 47:36.708
Look,

47:36.791 --> 47:38.750
I appreciate you,

47:38.833 --> 47:40.833
and everything
you done did for me.

47:40.916 --> 47:43.708
And Cindy is a great girl,

47:43.791 --> 47:45.458
really, really sweet.

47:45.541 --> 47:46.666
But,

47:46.750 --> 47:49.125
if you think we be more
than what we be...

47:49.208 --> 47:51.458
And what would that be?

47:51.541 --> 47:53.500
You helping me
with business and all.

47:53.583 --> 47:56.041
That make you an agent?

47:56.125 --> 47:57.791
I prefer to be a friend.

47:57.875 --> 48:00.291
How much cut a friend get?

48:00.375 --> 48:03.375
The only thing I want that
you can give me is your trust.

48:03.458 --> 48:06.291
We can let the money
come in time,

48:06.375 --> 48:08.458
once you've made plenty more.

48:11.541 --> 48:13.125
And Cindy?

48:14.958 --> 48:17.000
I ain't ready
to settle down yet.

48:20.291 --> 48:23.041
Son, I love my daughter
more than anyone.

48:23.125 --> 48:26.000
I want her to be happy.
But, me and you?

48:26.083 --> 48:28.583
Well, that's another
thing now, isn't it?

48:29.500 --> 48:31.583
- Business.
- That it is.

48:31.666 --> 48:33.583
And I don't see why
the end of one relationship

48:33.666 --> 48:35.500
should sacrifice the other.

48:38.000 --> 48:39.458
Right on.

48:40.541 --> 48:42.333
Think you could tell her for me?

48:43.375 --> 48:45.708
Hey, like you said.

48:45.791 --> 48:49.333
Magic ain't supposed to be
the one to give 'em bad news.

48:56.083 --> 48:58.083
I'll let her down light.

49:03.250 --> 49:06.041
Yeah, those is the Lakers,
not the Fakers.

49:06.125 --> 49:07.666
Hey, Black man, Black man,

49:07.750 --> 49:09.916
- Black man.
- Spencer, my main man.

49:10.000 --> 49:12.333
- Oh man.
- I know you've been living
